1. Coinbase sent a letter to US regulators, requesting a report on the clarity of banking services in the crypto industry;
2. Berachain mainnet will be launched on February 6;
3. Ionic suffered a loss of $8.6 million from the attack, and its predecessor Midas protocol was attacked twice;
4. AI Agent app store Olas received $13.8 million in financing, led by 1kx;
5. DePIN game infrastructure Beamable completed a $13.5 million Series A financing, led by Bitkraft Ventures;
6. Taproot Wizards completed a $30 million financing, led by Standard Crypto;
7. Justin Sun: Li Lin concealed due diligence materials when selling Huobi, and there was a $30 million hole inside;
8. Grayscale formally submitted the LTC ETF 19b-4 application;
9. David Sacks: Will promote regulation to ensure that innovation in the crypto field occurs in the United States;
10. Chairman of the U.S. House Financial Services Committee: Both houses of Congress will set up a cryptocurrency working group;
11. The SEC launched a new cryptocurrency task force website to "provide clarity on crypto regulations";
12. Crypto Tsar David Sacks: The feasibility of Bitcoin reserves is being studied;
13. Federal Reserve Jefferson: There is no need to rush to further cut interest rates, and a strong economy makes it appropriate to respond cautiously;
14. Crypto.com will submit an application for Cronos ETF and issue a new stablecoin;
15. Semler Scientific, a U.S. listed company, increased its holdings of 871 BTC for $88.5 million;
16. Solana's on-chain Meme project PAIN pre-sale raised 187,774 SOLs;
17. Musk: Some Reddit users' threats to DOGE employees are illegal, don't mess with DOGE.
